The '''Center for Environmental Technology''' or '''CET''', formerly known as the '''Environmental Technology Laboratory of NOAA, US Department of Commerce''', is a joint center between the [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]] (NOAA) and the [[University of Colorado at Boulder|University of Colorado]], which designs some of the most sensitive radio receivers in the world for active and passive microwave observation of terrestrial and atmospheric [[phenomenon|phenomena]].

