'''Institute of Physics and Power Engineering''' (full name: '''I.I. Leypunsky Institute of Physics and Power Engineering''', {{lang-ru|Государственный научный центр Российской Федерации Физико-энергетический институт, ГНЦ РФ-ФЭИ}}; '''IPPE''') is a [[research and development]] institute in the field of nuclear technology located in [[Obninsk]], Russia. It is a subsidiary of [[Rosatom]].

==History==
IPPE was established in May 1946 to develop nuclear power technology. The purpose of the Institute was the development of nuclear reactors and to solve scientific and engineering tasks in the field of nuclear power. The staff of the Institute had built the world's first nuclear power plant in Obninsk, [[Obninsk Nuclear Power Plant|AM-1]] ("Атом Мирный", Russian for Atom Mirny, or "peaceful atom"), was commissioned at IPPE on 27 June 1954.

==Developments==
During its existence the Institute has developed more than 120 different projects,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atomic-energy.ru/FEI|title= IPPE |date=2014-09-01|publisher= Atomic-Energy|accessdate=2014-10-11}}</ref> including:

•  the fast reactors [[BR-1 reactor|BR-1]], [[BR-2 reactor|BR-2]], [[BR-5 reactor|BR-5]], [[BR-10 reactor|BR-10]];

•  the reactor [[BOR-60 reactor|BOR-60]] in [[Research Institute of Atomic Reactors|RIAR]] ([[Dimitrovgrad, Russia|Dimitrovgrad]]);

•  the reactor [[BN-350 reactor]] for a nuclear power plant in [[Aktau]] ([[Kazakhstan]]);

•  the reactor [[BN-600 reactor]] and [[BN-800 reactor]] for [[Obninsk Nuclear Power Plant|Beloyarsk NPP]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.okbm.nnov.ru/english/beloyarsk-npp|title=  Beloyarskaya NPP|publisher=[[OKBM]]|accessdate=2014-10-16}}</ref>

•  the reactor [http://www.akmeengineering.com/svbr100.html SVBR-100 reactor];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gidropress.podolsk.ru/files/booklets/en/svbr75_100_en.pdf|title= SVBR-75/100 Nuclear Reactor|publisher=[[OKB Gidropress]]|accessdate=2014-10-16}}</ref>

•  space [[Beech nuclear reactor]] and [[TOPAZ nuclear reactor]];

•  naval [[Liquid metal cooled reactor|lead-bismuth liquid metal reactors]]: [[VT-1 reactor]], [[BM-40A reactor]], [[OK-550 reactor]]l

•  mobile nuclear power plant - TES-3 ([[:ru:ТЭС-3|ТЭС-3]])

== International Collaboration ==
The Institute collaborates with the leading scientific and research organizations of Russia, CIS and foreign countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nti.org/facilities/909/|title= IPPE |publisher=[[NTI]]|accessdate=2014-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.istc.ru/istc/db/inst.nsf/all/AA9BB05FE881A9CCC32565D700214624?opendocument|title= FEI (IPPE)|publisher=[[International Science and Technology Center|ISTC]]|accessdate=2014-10-16}}</ref> Among the most international projects can be named:

- involves on a large-scale project: [[Facility for Antiproton and Ion Research|FAIR]] | [http://www.fair-center.eu/partners/ru-russia.html FAIR-Russia].

- the cooperation with France concerning the creation of fast reactors;

- joint research with the USA, France, Germany, and Japan concerning reusing ex-nuclear materials of the reactor BH-600;

- joint project development of the fast reactor [[China Experimental Fast Reactor|CEFR]] with [[China]];

- joint project development of the fast reactor [[KALIMER reactor|KALIMER]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iaea.org/INPRO/cooperation/Second_IAEA-GIF_WS_on_SFRs/presentations/T5-Korea-Jeong.pdf|title=Design Concept of Korean Sodium-cooled Fast Reactor |date=2011-11-30|publisher=[[IAEA]]|accessdate=2014-10-17}}</ref> with [[South Korea]];

- interested in [[FBNR]] project;

