'''Michael Boxwell''' (born 1 February 1970) is an eco-technology author who has written the books ''[[Owning an Electric Car]]'', ''[[Solar Electricity Handbook]]'' and ''Proof of Delivery Buyer's Guide'', all published by Greenstream Publishing.<ref name="Greenstream Publishing">{{cite web |url=http://www.greenstreampublishing.com |title=Greenstream Publishing home page |publisher=Greenstream Publishing}}</ref>

He frequently appears on television<ref name="BBC">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/politics_show/8320259.stm |title=Electric cars failing to connect |publisher=BBC News |date=2009-10-22 |first=Peter |last=Plisner |accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref> and on radio talking about electric cars and co-hosted both the Transport Evolved<ref name="Transport Evolved">{{cite web |url=http://www.transportevolved.com |title=Transport Evolved : Transport Evolved Episode 5. Gullwings Are Sexy! |publisher=Transport Evolved  |date=2010-06-25 |accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref> show and TEN with [[Nikki Gordon-Bloomfield]]. Both shows are produced by Little Collie Ltd.<ref name="Little Collie Ltd">{{cite web|url=http://www.littlecollie.com |title=Little Collie Ltd |publisher=Littlecollie.com |date= |accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref>

Michael Boxwell lives in Warwickshire, England. He is married with two children.

