The '''nitronickelates''' are a class of chemical compounds containing a [[nickel]] atom complexed by [[nitro group]]s, -NO<sub>2</sub>. Nickel can be in a +2 or +3 oxidation state. There can be five ('''pentanitronickelates'''), or six, ('''hexanitronickelates''') nitro groups per nickel atom. The can be considered the double nitrites of [[nickel nitrite]].
